 of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’; the name of two famous 13th-century nuns of the Cistercian Abbey of Helfta near Eisleben, whose spiritual writings had a great influence."],"variants":[{"name":"Gertraud","meanings":["from <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’; the name of two famous 13th-century nuns of the Cistercian Abbey of Helfta near Eisleben, whose spiritual writings had a great influence."]},{"name":"Gertraut","meanings":["from <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’; the name of two famous 13th-century nuns of the Cistercian Abbey of Helfta near Eisleben, whose spiritual writings had a great influence."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":31,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King of the Kalmar Union. Sweden was upset with the Danes' interference with Swedish exports and unjust collection of taxes. The Engelbrekt Rebellion led to the deposing of Eric of Pomerania and the eventual dissolution of the Kalmar Union.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Ella Getrud Johansdotter was born in 1405, in Grangärde, Dalarna, Sweden, her father, Johan Hansson, was 30 and her mother, Kerstin Eriksdotter, was 30. She had at least 1 daughter with Staffan Andersson Hynninen. She died in 1480, in her hometown, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1405–1480":"1405–1480","1400–1475":"1400–1475","1437–1510":"1437–1510","1375–1450":"1375–1450","1437":"1437","1436":"1436","1510":"1510","1400":"1400","1475":"1475","1375":"1375","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","1405":"1405","Grangärde, Dalarna, Sverige":"Grangärde, Dalarna, Rootsi","Grangärde, Dalarna, Sweden":"Grangärde, Dalarna, Rootsi","By, Grangärde, Dalarna, Sverige":"By, Dalarna, Rootsi","Grangärde, Ludvika, Dalarna, Sverige":"Gran